Description: tree-based terminal session manager
 Tree Style Terminal is a GTK terminal emulator that organizes shell sessions
 in a hierarchical tree instead of a row of tabs.
 .
 Sessions can be nested, collapsed, renamed, and navigated with keyboard
 shortcuts. Each session uses the native VTE terminal widget and the user's
 normal shell environment.
